<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,158,905]" pageId="8" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,374,698,724]" pageId="8" pageNumber="232">Observation:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. S. Vega &amp; Rugolo. Both" authorityYear="2014" box="[374,659,698,724]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paucispiculata">
<emphasis box="[374,659,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="232">Chusquea paucispiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[860,960,699,725]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tovari">
<emphasis box="[860,960,699,725]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="232">C. tovari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which differs from the former by its wider foliage leaf blades 
<quantity box="[353,459,734,761]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.3" metricValueMax="6.6" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="232" unit="cm" value="5.3" valueMax="6.6" valueMin="4.0">4–6.6 cm</quantity>
lat., its greater synflorescences (75–) 
<quantity box="[884,1012,734,761]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.9" metricValueMax="10.8" metricValueMin="9.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="232" unit="cm" value="99.0" valueMax="108.0" valueMin="90.0">90–108 cm</quantity>
long and the palea that bears an acute apex, while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. S. Vega &amp; Rugolo. Both" authorityYear="2014" box="[301,499,770,797]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paucispiculata">
<emphasis box="[301,499,770,797]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="232">C. paucispiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is bimucronulate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,158,905]" pageId="8" pageNumber="232">
The micromorphological characters of foliage leaf blades of 
<taxonomicName box="[869,983,806,833]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parodii">
<emphasis box="[869,983,806,833]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="232">C. parodii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. S. Vega &amp; Rugolo. Both" authorityYear="2014" box="[1038,1236,806,833]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paucispiculata">
<emphasis box="[1038,1236,806,833]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="232">C. paucispiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are compared with those of related and sympatric species of 
<taxonomicName box="[602,885,842,868]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Platonia">
<emphasis box="[602,714,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="232">Chusquea</emphasis>
subg. 
<emphasis box="[789,885,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="232">Platonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. G. Clark." baseAuthorityName="L. G. Clark" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[903,1052,842,869]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laegaardii">
<emphasis box="[903,1052,842,869]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="232">C. laegaardii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. G. Clark" authorityYear="1996" box="[1107,1283,843,869]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Neurolepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="asymmetrica">
<emphasis box="[1107,1283,843,869]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="232">C. asymmetrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in 
<tableCitation box="[1329,1451,842,868]" captionStart-0="TABLE 1" captionStart-1="TABLE 2" captionStartId-0="8.[136,224,952,976]" captionStartId-1="9.[136,224,159,183]" captionText-0="TABLE 1. Comparative micromorphological characters of foliage leaf blade in transverse section among species of Chusquea subg. Platonia in Bolivia. VB, vascular bundles; +, present; -, absent;&gt;, greater." captionText-1="TABLE 2. Comparative micromorphological characters of foliage leaf blade abaxial epidermis among species of Chusquea subg. Platonia in Bolivia. +, present; ++, abundant; -, absent." pageId="8" pageNumber="232">Tables 1–2</tableCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[183,291,878,905]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 5" captionStart-1="FIGURE 6" captionStartId-0="10.[136,229,1928,1950]" captionStartId-1="11.[136,229,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox-0="[162,1425,175,1918]" captionTargetBox-1="[220,1368,191,1933]" captionTargetId-0="figure-19@10.[162,1425,175,1918]" captionTargetId-1="figure-24@11.[220,1368,191,1933]" captionTargetPageId-0="10" captionTargetPageId-1="11" captionText-0="FIGURE 5. Foliage leaf blade transverse section LM micrographs. Chusquea asymmetrica. A. Keel [from Beck 17683 (SI)]. B. General view [from Beck 17683 (SI)]. C. Margin [from Clark 1113 (AAU)]. Chusquea laegaardii [from Beck 24403 (SI)]. D. Keel. E. General view. Chusquea parodii [from Beck 26221 (SI)]. F. Keel. G. General view. H. Margin. Chusquea paucispiculata [from Beck 26225 (SI)]. I. Keel. J. General view. K. Margin. Scale bars = 200 μm for D, 100 μm for all others.Abbreviations: Bc, bulliform cells; Scl, sclerenchyma; VB1, first order vascular bundle; VB2, second order vascular bundle; VB3, third order vascular bundle." captionText-1="FIGURE 6. Foliage leaf blade abaxial epidermis SEM micrographs. Chusquea asymmetrica [from Clark 1113 (AAU)]. A. General view. B. Detail of furrow. Chusquea laegaardii [from Laegaard 101905B (AAU)]. C. General view. D. Detail of stomata. Chusquea parodii [from Beck 26221 (SI)]. E. General view. F. Detail of stomata. Chusquea paucispiculata [from Beck 26225 (SI)]. G. General view. H. Detail of prickle hair. Scale bars = 100 μm for C, G and H, 50 μm for A and E, 20 μm for B and D, 10 μm for F.Abbreviations: In, inflated long cell; Mi, microhair; Pa, papillae; Pr, prickle; St, stomata." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5151644" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5151650" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5151644/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5151650/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="232">Figs. 5–6</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
